Use Cases :
Managing User Session - Authentication
Managing Session Data - UserIds SessionId UserPreferences

In Memory Caching to increase throughput between inter-microservice calls

Under the hood - it is a distributed hash table which maps object value to keys spread across multiple nodes
The Distributed Hash Table allows Distributed Cache to scale on the fly.
It manages the addition, deletion, failure of nodes continuously as long as the Cache service is live.

MemCache - Google
